  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6596.81 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-25.9B) and positive gamma resistance at 6605 (+27.5B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push above 6605. The breakout regime with -20.2B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, but the tight 15-point range between these opposing gamma walls is creating explosive hedging flows as evidenced by the 59% 1-minute GEX surge. Key battle lines are 6590 (where dealer buying accelerates) and 6605 (where dealer selling kicks in), with a break of either level likely triggering violent momentum in that direction.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves as price ping-pongs between 6590 support and 6605 resistance until one breaks decisively.",
